I've had the GS77 for about 4 months now and I think it's pretty terrible in a lot of ways. When first setting it up my laptop crashed due to high temperature. The automatic feature for the fan attempts to keep the fan fairly quiet, but you will have to set the fan setting to "Cooler Boost" if you want to pay any games at a decent setting. There is nothing stealthy about this laptop if you want to do anything more then watch videos on it. It runs extremely hot. It is actually extremely loud while on "Cooler Boost". Without "Cooler Boost" you will feel great travel to the keyboard keys within ten minutes while paying any demanding game.Video quality is significantly worse than my previous Gamer's Republic G5. 1080p does not look like 1080p. It's as if the picture was designed for a smaller resolution, then they decided to stretch that same picture on a larger screen.I had trouble connecting my expensive Razer headphones to this laptop which I hadn't experienced with a gaming laptop, especially since my headphones are wired. Long story short I had to deep dive into the audio settings and disable an MSI audio program which was automatically competing with my headphones.Would not recommend.

I would stay away from MSI. They are a horrible company. I purchased a GS76 Stealth 11UH-029 17.3” FHD Gaming Laptop with Extended Warranty - 2 Years for $3,239.99. The laptop broke by fault of MSI hardware within 7 months of owning it and I had to send it in for a repair. When they repaired it, they caused another problem with the licensure of Windows and I had to redownload all the drivers manually with MSI on the phone. Another hardware problem came up and I had to send it in for a repair again. I have been without this laptop for over three months. Bernabe Nunez is very unresponsive and they will not give me a refund. Finally, they shipped it to the wrong location and guaranteed me an extension on my warranty and have failed to follow through. STAY FAR AWAY FROM MSI. I hope my accurate review will spare anyone else the extreme frustration MSI has caused me.
